@dgquintas, @markdroth: are you able to take a look?  I think this one should be fairly uncontroversial.
Jenkins, this is ok to test
@yallop : thanks for your contribution and I think we can review it. Can you also create a matching issue describing this problem? I think most of the PR description above can be moved to the issue .
@vjpai: I've opened #12075.
![Pony expressing approval](http://i0.kym-cdn.com/photos/images/original/000/284/941/1a2.png)

```
[trickle] No significant performance differences
```

```
[microbenchmarks] No significant performance differences
```
Now, interestingly, there are about 6 other anonymous structs/unions in gRPC core headers besides the ones in this pull request. Do you not need names on those?

I'm thinking, for example, of the `default_level` and `default_algorithm` fields of `compression_types.h` ; these are exposed to language wrappers (and are used in other language bindings like Ruby) but don't have a type name.

@vjpai: got it; thanks!  I've added tags for the remaining types (72b8ed4) and rebased against master.

I can add a sanity check to the branch, too (https://github.com/grpc/grpc/issues/12075#issuecomment-320480517), if someone directs me to the appropriate place to add the code.
I wrote a sanity check in #12095, but it isn't working for some reason that I don't understand, so I'm going to try to get that solved so that we can merge this together with that.
